                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/286: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-23T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April 24, 3.34 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>National Legislative Assembly yesterday passed bill authorizing each bank to set
                    aside 10,000,000 pesos of a new issue for a fund to be used in agricultural and
                    building loans at 4 per cent. It now awaits presidential approval which will be
                    given as the measure is of his own making. This means sixty millions additional
                    in controvertible [<hi rend="italic">convertible</hi>] paper.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
